A R E S O L U T I O N
Honoring the Ohio Division of State Fire Marshal on
its One Hundred Twenty-fifth Anniversary.
WHEREAS, The members of the Senate of the 136th General Assembly 1
of Ohio are pleased to pay tribute to the Ohio Division of State Fire 2
Marshal on the One Hundred Twenty-fifth Anniversary of its founding; 3
and 4
WHEREAS, Recognition of this event is a fitting tribute to the 5
Ohio Division of State Fire Marshal, for since its inception, this 6
praiseworthy organization has achieved an admirable record of service 7
to the whole of our state. Established in 1900 through Senate Bill 51, 8
the agency has been a vital instrument for safety, responding to even 9
the most challenging of circumstances with professionalism, and its 10
commitment to excellence has been clearly visible in all of its 11
endeavors; and 12
WHEREAS, Over the past one hundred twenty-five years, the Ohio 13
Division of State Fire Marshal has witnessed many changes in the field 14
of emergency services, and it has worked diligently to keep pace with 15
these challenges. Indeed, the agency’s achievements are an outstanding 16
reflection not only on the department itself but also on its numerous 17
professionals over the years and on the entire state; and 18
WHEREAS, While many people are content to take a passive role in 19
life, the members of the Ohio Division of State Fire Marshal have 20
proven to be some of the finest individuals in this challenging and 21
paramount field, and the enthusiasm and devotion to duty that they 22
have shown have gained them the gratitude and appreciation of the many 23
they have served. We are certain that as they maintain their 24
dedication to service, these individuals will continue in the 25
tradition of excellence which has long been the department’s hallmark; 26

